---
const sponsorUrl = "https://github.com/sponsors/jmanuelrosa";
---

<section id="support" class="px-6 pb-20 sm:pb-28" data-section="support">
  <div class="prose-column">
    <p class="sectionrule">Support</p>
    <h2 class="display-lg">
      Free forever. <span class="hl">Optionally sponsored.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="lede mt-6">
      trakdown is MIT-licensed and free for everyone — no paid tier, no account
      wall, no telemetry beyond anonymous landing-page analytics. If it earns a
      spot in your workflow and you want to keep the AI work moving, GitHub
      Sponsors is open.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a
        href={sponsorUrl}
        class="btn btn-ghost"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        data-umami-event="sponsor_click"
        data-umami-event-location="support-section"
      >Sponsor on GitHub →</a>
    </div>
    <p class="small mt-6">
      Zero-dollar contributions count too — a star, an issue, or a Chrome Web
      Store review help just as much.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
